-------> BEHAVIOUR (10min)

Each week we will have a 10 minute discussion about the behaviours that are expected of true Christians

Behaviour describes the actions we take. Our habits, and the way we conduct ourselves each day. The things we do

If reading scripture is the theory component, behaviours are the application component

The goal isn't just to know Gods word, it's to apply the word in everyday life. Behaviours are the actions we take

Each week we will choose a behaviour to discuss and today we're talking about the behaviour of reading the bible



Before we can apply Gods word and live righteously, we must first know and understand his word

The way we do that is reading the source material which is the Bible

The Bible isn't a normal book that you read cover to cover and are done with it

I approach the Bible as the source material textbook for a lifelong research project

The aim of the project is to live righteously according to the word of God and the methodology is to read the word daily and seek to apply the lessons as an operating system for life

I think the only thing I can say with certainty is that to be a true Christian you must read the bible

You shouldn't rely on others to tell you what the bible says and how you should behave

You should read it yourself and you should read it regularly


Frequency (how often do you read the bible)

Depth (reading the words vs understaning the lessons)


Reflections: 
- Are you actively readinf the bible? If so, how frequently are you reading?
- Are you reading to check the box off or are you reading to understand?
- How is readinf the bible informing or changing your daily behaviours?

Know -> Understand -> Apply -> Teach



